            <title>[HBASE-685] [Performance] Alternative to synchronized SortedMap</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-685</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-684&quot; title=&quot;unnecessary iteration in HMemcache.internalGet? got much better reading performance after break it.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-684&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-684&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, LN suggests that we should find alternative to synchronized sortedmap; its used all over the place in hbase so a faster alternative should improve thoughput.  That synchronized sortedmap is less than perfect has been known from earliest days (see cafarella comment at head of HStore#internalGet in 0.1 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
